					Full Description



IMH Financial Corporation (IMHFC), incorporated on December 22, 2009, is a real estate investor and finance company based in the southwest United States. The Company's segments include Hospitality and Entertainment Operations, which consists of two operating hotels in Sedona, Arizona with related spa, and food and beverage operations, and a golf course operation located in Bullhead City, Arizona with related spa, and food and beverage operations; Mortgage and real estate owned (REO)Legacy Portfolio and Other Operations, which consists of activities relating to the collection, workout and sale of new and legacy loans and REO assets, including financing of such asset sales; Commercial Real Estate Leasing Operations, which consists of a commercial medical office building located in Stafford, Texas, and Corporate and Other, which consists of the Company's centralized general and administrative, corporate treasury and deposit gathering activities, and interest expense associated with debt issuances.The Company's focus is to invest in, originate, manage and dispose of commercial real estate mortgage and related investments. It also focuses to perform functions related thereto, including developing, managing and either holding for investment or disposing of real property acquired through foreclosure, investment or other means.As of December 31, 2014, the Company's loan portfolio consisted of nine first mortgage loans. Of its nine outstanding loans as of December 31, 2014, the Company had three performing loans.

» Full Overview of IPO-IFC.N







